title: ITS DA BUTTON
html_content:
Chris, content with his accomplishment.

ITS DA BUTTON is a video Chris uploaded on 31 August 2024. In it, he celebrates receiving his YouTube Silver Play Button plaque, which was awarded for getting 100,000 subscribers.

Transcript

 This media needs a transcript. Help CWCki by transcribing the content. If the media is too long, transcribe select portions which are funny or informative.

Hey everybody, this is Jesus Christine Weston Chandler Sonichu Prime coming in once again, and today something very, very special that all of you are aware of... we have reached over [Chris puts his hands to his face and soys out.] one hundred thousand subscribers! One hundred subscriber! One hundred thousand subscribers! Yeah! (chuckle) And so, checked my E-mail and the, uh, code... which I redeemed and... [Chris imitates a trumpet and reveals the box of the YouTube Play Button to the camera.] In this box, which we have covered the receiving address cuz we want no doxing... is a lovely little putton. So- [Chris stammers.] about to say, a big ol' YouTube on there, it's black. There's the top, there's the bottom, there's one side, there's the other side, eh... No obligatory product shots at the back! Heh. It's an unboxing video, so we're gonna... unbox this video.

[Video cuts to Chris opening the box with scissors.]
Watch this, so... One piece of tape there! One piece of tape there... and, uh... and the code is apparently only sent out to those who have reached that milestone, so yes...

[Video cuts to Chris holding a card.]
 Hm, we got a card. [Chris starts to read a message from YouTube staff.] Congratulations on your subscriber milestone! We our honored to take part in recognizing your achievement and want your experience to be ecceptional! This award was inspected by packaged with care by... name on the card, but shall not be disclosed because I do not like doxing anybody. But it was made by Society Awards... and a letter is included, ist... Do you remember your first subscriber? Your one hundredth? Or your one thousandth? Chances are... you do... [Chris smiles at the camera.] And you know that you will definitely remember your one hundredth thousand subscriber! Your fans may have found you while searching YouTube, learned about you through a friend, or maybe you showed up as a recommended video. No matter how they came to your channel, your audience stayed and their numbers increased because of you and the community you've built. We are proud to honor your impressive milestone of reaching one hundred thousand subscribers with the Silver Creator Award. Congratulations! We know you have many more stories to share with your community, and we know that your fans can't wait for you to amaze them even more with your commitment and creativity. So keep creating, keep building, we can't wait to see what you'll do next and we're here to support you along the way. Who knows, when you reach your millionth subscriber... [Chris stammers.] Do you remember your one hundredth thousandth... your sincerely, the YouTube CEO... [Chris shows the letter to the camera.] And there's the letter...

[Video cuts to Chris unwrapping the Play Button.]
Pulling it out of the plastic sleeve... [Chris imitates a trumpet and holds the Play Button to his face.] It's a button! No two buttons about it. Hm, [Chris leans forward and puts the Play Button to the camera, the reflection of the button showing Chris's recording software on his computer.] can you see yourself, in this yourself, in this yourself, in this yourself... Hm, very nice, yes indeed. This shall be handled with care.
